Voltage-mode approach employs the V-I droop characteristic which uses the measured branch current to generate the terminal voltage reference. The control scheme for voltage-mode droop-controlled VSC is shown in Fig. 10. As expressed in (3), the DC voltage reference is generated according to the branch output DC current using the V-I droop characteristic:3Vdc∗=Vo-Idck\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ V_{dc}^{*} = V_{o} - I_{dc} k $$\end{document}where Vo is the nominal bus voltage; k is the droop gain; Idc is the DC current measurement; Vdc* is the generated DC voltage reference.Fig. 10
Voltage-mode droop control scheme

